Write a simple algorithm to rank a list of items from highest to lowest. Input: {5000, 1800, 9001, 1100, 67} 1. Start by sorting the list of items in descending order. 2. Take the first item from the unsorted list and compare it to the items in the sorted list. 3. If it is greater than the first item in the sorted list, insert it at the beginning of the sorted list. 4. If it is smaller than the first item in the sorted list, continue to compare it with the next items in the sorted list until you find an item that is smaller than it. 5. Insert the item from the unsorted list before the smaller item in the sorted list. 6. Repeat Steps 2-5 until all items from the unsorted list have been inserted into the sorted list in the correct order. 7. The final sorted list will be displayed in descending order. In this case, the list {5000, 1800, 9001, 1100, 67} will be sorted as follows: {9001, 5000, 1800, 1100, 67}

Make a list of 5 ingredients that would make a great pizza.
